{{Politics of San Marino}}
'''Ideas in Motion''' ({{lang-it|Idee in Movimento}}, IM) was a left-wing political party in [[San Marino]].
==History== The party was established in 1998 by [[Alessandro Rossi (Captains Regent)|Alessandro Rossi]] as a successor to the [[Democratic Movement (San Marino)|Democratic Movement]], which had won two seats in the [[Sammarinese general election, 1993|1993 elections]].<ref name=TL>Tom Lansford (2015) ''Political Handbook of the World 2015'', CQ Press</ref> It contested the [[Sammarinese general election, 1998|elections later that year]] in an alliance with the [[Sammarinese Democratic Progressive Party]] (PPDS) and the [[Democratic Convention (San Marino)|Democratic Convention]]. The alliance received 18.6% of the vote, winning 11 of the 60 seats in the [[Grand and General Council]], becoming the third-largest faction.
In 2001 it merged with the PPDS and [[Socialists for Reform]] to form the [[Party of Democrats]].<ref name=TL/>
