'''The Archdiocese of Niamey''' is a [[Roman Catholic]] [[Archdiocese]] in [[Niger]]. It is based in the capital city of [[Niamey]] and was erected on 28 April 1942. [[Pope Benedict XVI]] made it an [[archdiocese]] in June 2007. It performs the [[Latin Rite]] and covers approximately {{convert|200,000|km2|mi2|sigfig=1}}.

As of 2004, the diocese population was about 5,880,000 with 0.3% Catholic. 29 priests were in the Diocese for a ratio of 517 Catholics per Priest. [[Djalwana Laurent Lompo]] has been the head of the archdiocese since October 2014. 

==External links==
