{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Daloa |latin = Dioecesis Daloaensis |country = {{flag|Côte d'Ivoire}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Gagnoa|Gagnoa]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |area_km2 = 25,000 |population = 1,196,000 |population_as_of = 2006 |catholics = 38,000 |catholics_percent= 3.2 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Maurice Konan Kouassi]] }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Daloa''' ({{lang-la|Dalaoaën(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Daloa]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Gagnoa|Gagnoa]] in [[Côte d'Ivoire]].
==History== * April 9, 1940: Established as Apostolic Vicariate of Sassandra from the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Costa d’Avorio]] * September 14, 1955: Promoted as Diocese of Daloa
==Special churches== The [[Cathedral]] is the Cathédrale du Christ-Roi in Daloa.
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Daloa (Roman rite) ** Bishop Maurice Konan Kouassi (since 2005.03.22) ** Bishop [[Pierre-Marie Coty]] (1975.11.20 – 2005.03.22) ** Bishop [[Pierre-Eugène Rouanet]], [[Society of African Missions|S.M.A.]] ** Bishop [[Jean Marie Etrillard]], S.M.A. (1956.02.29 – 1956.07.04) * Vicars Apostolic of Sassandra (Roman rite) ** Bishop [[Alphonse Charles Kirmann]], S.M.A. (1940.04.09 – 1955.03.25)
