'''Sibut Airport''' {{Airport codes||FEFU}} is an [[airstrip]] serving [[Sibut]], a city in the [[Kémo]] prefecture of the [[Central African Republic]]. The airstrip is {{convert|2|km}} southwest of the town. It was built after January 2014<ref>Google Earth Historical Imagery 1/1/2014</ref> and replaces a long closed airport east of Sibut.
