'''Vlekete''' or '''Verekete''' is a [[deity]] and goddess of the sea in the [[mythology]] of the [[Badagry|people of Badagry]].<ref>{{cite book|author=L. C. Dioka|title=Lagos and Its Environs|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9pUPAQAAMAAJ|year=2001|publisher=First Academic|isbn=978-978-34902-5-3}}</ref> Velekete has a shrine named after it called the Velekete Shrine and a slave market called [[Velekete Slave Market]].<ref>{{cite book|author=Ashamu Sewanu Fadipe|title=Commerce D'esclaves Et la Civilisation Occidentale À Badagry|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D5UPAQAAMAAJ|year=2000|publisher=Media Ace|isbn=978-978-33660-3-9}}</ref>

